meat--literally, "victuals," as for a journey.

[Psalms 78:29](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#029.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_029">psa 78:29</span></span>

their . . . desire--what they longed for.

[Psalms 78:30](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#030.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_030">psa 78:30</span></span>

not estranged . . . lust--or, "desire"--that is, were indulging it.

[Psalms 78:31](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#031.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_031">psa 78:31</span></span>

slew . . . fattest--or, "among the fattest"; some of them--

chosen--the young and strong ([Isa
40:31](../../../bib/kjv/isa040.htm#031).md), and so none could resist.

[Psalms 78:33](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#033.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_033">psa 78:33</span></span>

Though there were partial reformations after chastisement, and God, in
pity, withdrew His hand for a time, yet their general conduct was
rebellious, and He was thus provoked to waste and destroy them, by long
and fruitless wandering in the desert.

[Psalms 78:36](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#036.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_036">psa 78:36</span></span>

lied . . . tongues--a feigned obedience ([Psa
18:44](../../../bib/kjv/psa018.htm#044).md).

[Psalms 78:37](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#037.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_037">psa 78:37</span></span>

heart . . . not right--or, "firm" (compare [Psa
78:8](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#008.md); [Psa
51:10](../../../bib/kjv/psa051.htm#010).md).

[Psalms 78:39](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#039.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_039">psa 78:39</span></span>

