[Psalms 78:40](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#040.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_040">psa 78:40</span></span>

There were ten temptations ([Num
14:22](../../../bib/kjv/num014.htm#022).md).

[Psalms 78:41](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#041.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_041">psa 78:41</span></span>

limited--as in [Psa 78:19-20](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#019.md). Though
some prefer "grieved" or "provoked." The retreat from Kadesh ([Deu
1:19-23](../../../bib/kjv/deu001.htm#019).md) is meant, whether--

turned--be for turning back, or to denote repetition of offense.

[Psalms 78:43](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#043.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_043">psa 78:43</span></span>

