[Psalms 78:45](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#045.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_045">psa 78:45</span></span>

The dog-fly or the mosquito.

[Psalms 78:46](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#046.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_046">psa 78:46</span></span>

caterpillar--the Hebrew name, from its voracity, and that of--

locust--from its multitude.

[Psalms 78:47](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#047.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_047">psa 78:47</span></span>

The additional effects of the storm here mentioned (compare [Exo
9:23-34](../../../bib/kjv/exo009.htm#023).md) are consistent with Moses'
account.

[Psalms 78:48](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#048.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_048">psa 78:48</span></span>

gave . . . cattle--literally, "shut up" (compare [Psa
31:8](../../../bib/kjv/psa031.htm#008).md).

[Psalms 78:49](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#049.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_049">psa 78:49</span></span>

evil angels--or, "angels of evil"--many were perhaps employed, and other
evils inflicted.

[Psalms 78:50](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#050.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_050">psa 78:50</span></span>

