([Sa2 1:22](../../../bib/kjv/sa2001.htm#022.md); [Hos
7:16](../../../bib/kjv/hos007.htm#016).md). They relapsed.

[Psalms 78:58](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#058.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_058">psa 78:58</span></span>

Idolatry resulted from sparing the heathen (compare [Psa
78:9-11](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#009).md).

[Psalms 78:59](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#059.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_059">psa 78:59</span></span>

heard--perceived ([Gen 11:7](../../../bib/kjv/gen011.htm#007).md).

abhorred--but not utterly.

[Psalms 78:60](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#060.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_060">psa 78:60</span></span>

tent . . . placed--literally, "caused to dwell," set up ([Jos
18:1](../../../bib/kjv/jos018.htm#001).md).

[Psalms 78:61](../../../bib/kjv/psa078.htm#061.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_061">psa 78:61</span></span>

his strength--the ark, as symbolical of it ([Psa
